<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN333">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nīruṭ paṭṭa mārip pēruṟai</l>
<l>mokku ḷaṉṉa pokuṭṭuviḻik kaṇṇa</l>
<l>karumpiṭart talaiya peruñcevik kuṟumuya</l>
<l>luḷḷūrk kuṟumputaṟ ṟuḷḷuvaṉa vukaḷun</l>
<l>toḷḷai maṉṟat tāṅkaṭ paṭari</l>
<l>ṉuṇkeṉa vuṇarā vuyaviṟ ṟāyiṉun</l>
<l>taṅkiṉir ceṉmō pulavir naṉṟuñ</l>
<l>ceṉṟataṟ koṇṭu maṉaiyōḷ virumpi</l>
<l>varakun tiṉaiyu muḷḷavai yellā</l>
<l>miravaṉ mākka ḷuṇakkoḷat tīrnteṉak</l>
<l>kuṟittumā ṟetirppai peṟāa maiyiṟ</l>
<l>kuraluṇaṅku vitaittiṉai yuralvāyp peytu</l>
<l>ciṟitu puṟappaṭṭaṉ ṟōvila ṭaṉṉūr</l>
<l>vēṭṭak kuṭitoṟuṅ kūṭṭu........</l>
<l>............................... uṭumpucey</l>
<l>pāṇi neṭuntēr vallarō ṭūrā</l>
<l>vampaṇi yāṉai vēntutalai variṉu</l>
<l>muṇpatu maṉṉu matuvē</l>
<l>pariciṉ maṉṉuṅ kuricilkoṇ  ṭatuvē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>When you set out for that place with a village common with holes,</l>
<l>where the little hares with large ears, heads with black napes</l>
<l>[and] bud eyes like bubbles</l>
<l>of big rain drop when they fall into the water</l>
<l>hop [and] frolick among the little bushes of the inner villages,</l>
<l>even if it is a troubled place where you don’t perceive [them saying] “please eat!”,</l>
<l>stay [there and] go, you scholars.</l>
<l>The lady of the house, much desirous of taking what is gone,</l>
<l>because all that was there of millet and millet</l>
<l>was finished, when she took [it] so that the mendicant folk would eat,</l>
<l>[and] because of not obtaining the return of the exchange intended,</l>
<l>pours into the mortar the millet [meant] for seed drying on the ears</l>
<l>[and] does not turn [her] back at all.</l>
</lg>
